oacNatMIBModule.name: oacNatMIBModule

revisions.description: Added NOTIFICATION-TYPE, and fixed minor corrections.
This MIB module describes IPSec Managed objects.

oacIPSecSAcreated.name: oacIPSecSAcreated
oacIPSecSAcreated.description: An IPSec SA created notification signifies that the device created an IPSec security association.

oacIPSecSAremoved.name: oacIPSecSAremoved
oacIPSecSAremoved.description: An IPSec SA removed notification signifies that the device removed an IPSec security association.

oacIPSecCmapEnabled.name: oacIPSecCmapEnabled
oacIPSecCmapEnabled.description: An IPSec crypto map enabled notification signifies that the device validated the crypto map attached to an interface and the crypto map becomes valid on this interface.

oacIPSecCmapDisabled.name: oacIPSecCmapDisabled
oacIPSecCmapDisabled.description: An IPSec crypto map disabled notification signifies that the device did not validate the crypto map attached to an interface and the crypto map becomes invalid on this interface.

oacIPSecCpolEnabled.name: oacIPSecCpolEnabled
oacIPSecCpolEnabled.description: An IPSec crypto map policy enabled notification signifies that the device validated the crypto map policy. configuration is considered as active and can be used by Isakmp daemon, or IPSec manual keying.

oacIPSecCpolDisabled.name: oacIPSecCpolDisabled
oacIPSecCpolDisabled.description: An IPSec crypto map policy disabled notification signifies that the device did not validate the crypto map policy. Configuration is considered as inactive and can not be used by Isakmp or manual IPSec manual keying.

oacIPSecHwModuleDown.name: oacIPSecHwModuleDown
oacIPSecHwModuleDown.description: An IPSec hardware module down notification signifies that the device can not use any hardware encryption module, because it is not activated, or it is not present on the device.

oacISAKMPBadProposal.name: oacISAKMPBadProposal
oacISAKMPBadProposal.description: An ISAKMP bad proposal notification signifies that the device did not validate proposal for IPSec phase 1 with a remote peer.

oacISAKMPNoResponse.name: oacISAKMPNoResponse
oacISAKMPNoResponse.description: An ISAKMP No Response notification signifies that the device was exchanging ISAKMP information with a remote ISAKMP peer, and the peer did not give any answer to the device.

oacISAKMPConnectionEstablished.name: oacISAKMPConnectionEstablished
oacISAKMPConnectionEstablished.description: An ISAKMP Connection established notification signifies that the device established an ISAKMP connection with a remote ISAKMP device.

oacISAKMPConnectionRemoved.name: oacISAKMPConnectionRemoved
oacISAKMPConnectionRemoved.description: An ISAKMP Connection removed notification signifies that the device removed an ISAKMP connection with a remote ISAKMP device, because the lifetime of the connection reached the limit, or a reset has been carried out on the device, either by using clear crypto isakmp sa, or by shutting down the IPSec working interface.

oacISAMPIPSecConnectionEstablished.name: oacISAMPIPSecConnectionEstablished
oacISAMPIPSecConnectionEstablished.description: An ISAKMP IPSec Connection established notification signifies that the ISAKMP daemon of the device successfully created an IPSec tunnel between two ISAKMP peers.

oacISAKMPIPSecConnectionRemoved.name: oacISAKMPIPSecConnectionRemoved
oacISAKMPIPSecConnectionRemoved.description: An ISAKMP IPSec Connection removed notification signifies that the ISAKMP daemon of the device removed an IPSec connection, either because the lifetime of the IPSec session reached the limit, or because a reset has been carried out on the IPSec working interface of the device.

oacISAKMPUnknownPeer.name: oacISAKMPUnknownPeer
oacISAKMPUnknownPeer.description: An ISAKMP unknown peer notification signifies that the device received an unknown isakmp request and did not process it.

oacISAKMPNotificationMsgReceived.name: oacISAKMPNotificationMsgReceived
oacISAKMPNotificationMsgReceived.description: An ISAKMP notification message received notification signifies that the device received a notification from a known ISAKMP peer.

oacISAKMPNotificationMsgSent.name: oacISAKMPNotificationMsgSent
oacISAKMPNotificationMsgSent.description: An ISAKMP notification message sent notification signifies that the device sent a notification to a known ISAKMP peer. Generally, a sent notification is due to a problem on the ISAKMP connection between two ISAKMP peers. For example, if received packet is malformed, a notification message is sent.

oacISAKMPDeadPeerDetected.name: oacISAKMPDeadPeerDetected
oacISAKMPDeadPeerDetected.description: An ISAKMP Dead Peer detection signifies that the device detected a DPD when using ISAKMP keepalive.
